Relatives of those onboard Malaysia Airlines Flight MH370 have endured days of anxious waiting under an intense media spotlight and some appeared to begin to accept that their loved ones may not have survived.Scores of Chinese family members are waiting for news at a Beijing hotel. Flight MH370 had 150 Chinese passengers onboard when it departed Beijing on Saturday at 1.20am local time, bound for Kuala Lumpur.Malaysia Airlines has offered to fly two relatives of each missing person to Kuala Lumpur to be closer to the search.A representative from the airline confirmed that 12 had left on Tuesday, but the airline had said on Monday that it was "deploying an additional aircraft" to Beijing to transport relatives.The search for the missing Boeing 777 has now been extended to the Strait of Malacca, where the Malaysian Air Force picked up the last radar trace of the aircraft.